intro: Utricularia albiflora var. quinquedentata, commonly known as the white-flowered bladderwort, is a carnivorous plant belonging to the family Lentibulariaceae. It is characterized by its small, delicate leaves and specialized bladder-like structures used to trap prey. This variety is native to wetland and aquatic environments in Southeast Asia. The plant produces small, white flowers that are typically borne in clusters. Its botanical features make it an interesting subject for studies on carnivorous plant adaptations and ecological interactions.
